The paper deals with the effectiveness of active cyber defense, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed model involves stochastic processes and mathematical analysis, which are typical of the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the mean-field approximation, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.NI.
